POUILLY-FUISSE 1997
Greatly influenced by the distinctive soil type, mineral and
plant-based aromas, as well as walnut and grilled almonds
complimented by a floral touch with a hint of honey. Rich
and generous, with mineral undertones confirming the
origins of this distinctive Pouilly - Fuisse. Although Pouilly -
Fuisse is often prefered young to better appreciate is
distinctive aromas.

CHATEAU STE MICHELLE
Pure red fruit aromas cherry and raspberry introduce this
wine, accented with vanilla and sweet cider. A find balance
of oak and fruit emerges on the palate. Rich and supple,
with flavors of ripe raspberry, cherry cider and smooth oak,
this Merlot is delightfully soft.

CHATEAU STE MICHELLE
Mike januik crafted the 1998 vintage to showcase the
distinctive aromas and flavos of this vinevard. The wine was
sur lie aged for 10 months after fermentation in 100%
French oak barrel.
A balanced wine with classic apple and spice notes and
citrus flavors. The viscous, silky mouthfeel is enhanced by a
long and generous finish.
